Method Detail

findByExample

List findByExample(Object exampleObject)
Deprecated. will be removed in the next version

Find all objects of the type associated with this DAO based on the provided example object and return them in a List. Any non-null properties will be matched exactly and any null values will be ignored.

Note: even though this method accepts any object, you should only give it the associated persistent object type.

Note: If you use primitive types in your persistent objects then those values cannot be null and must be set to something or the example matches will not work the way you expect.

Parameters:
exampleObject - - an example object which should have null for any properties which should not be matched and
Returns:
a List of 0 or more persistent objects

findByExample

List findByExample(Object exampleObject,
                   int firstResult,
                   int maxResults)
Deprecated. will be removed in the next version

Find all objects of the type associated with this DAO based on the provided example object and return them in a List. Any non-null properties will be matched exactly and any null values will be ignored.

Order is not guaranteed.

Parameters:
exampleObject - - an example object which should have null for any properties which should not be matched and
firstResult - - the index of the first result object to be retrieved (numbered from 0)
maxResults - - the maximum number of result objects to retrieve (or <=0 for no limit)
Returns:
a List of 0 or more persistent objects
See Also:
